reviews.review_text:
Ironically,  a very well played show.. Well,  just for the record; this was the worst sounding Grateful Dead show I ever attended in my dead career.  Yes,  it was my hometown show and all my cool friends were going; even my dad said, be careful; there's gonna be a bunch of undercover cops out there.  He was right , a bunch of fans arrested for this that and the other... made the newspaper and TV news the next day ; "they just won't let us be" !  

However, it was a sultry hot summer Kentucky day and night with plenty of humidity.  I had learned later after the show that the GD sound crew had employed extra labor from UPS to move PA since the local stage hands union was not in the mood or "contract" .  Hence,  the sound of this show was terrible , muddy, low volume, but extremely well played.  I can't blame the sound of any taper out there for this show,  only a soundboard is worthy of a listen.  WHY hasn't this show been offered for a release ? Yes,  only a portion of the video feed has been released of the He's Gone Jam , but the whole show is really well played.  If you want a good recording please petition the GDM to release the whole show ... I"m in !
